      "id": 999,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Audit Log Aggregation — Roadmap\n\n**Live audit log:** Vault writes JSONL to `/vault/logs/audit.log` inside `vault-server`. Operator + sidecar reads land here in real time. The platform retains 30 days locally; nightly archive to QNAP.\n\n**Why this dashboard doesn't tail it inline:** Streaming a JSONL file into Grafana panels needs a log-aggregator (Loki + Promtail, or Vector → VictoriaLogs). That infrastructure is **not** deployed. Adding it would expand Block 2 scope materially, so it is **deferred** to a logs-focused phase.\n\n**Today's verification path** (operator runbook):\n```\ndocker exec vault-server tail -f /vault/logs/audit.log | jq -c '{time, type, request: {operation, path, remote_address}, response: {error}}'\n```\n\n**When logs aggregation lands**, this panel will be replaced with:\n- Auth attempts by mount (success/failure split)\n- Top accessed paths (last 24h)\n- Failed operations timeline (state-timeline)\n- Token creates / revokes by entity\n\nSee `docs/phase-13/PHASE_13_BLOCK_2_PLAN.md` for the explicit scope boundary.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Audit Log Tailing — Deferred",
      "type": "text"
    }
